  "entity_type": "vehicle",
  "overview": {
    "value": "Angara A5 is a Russian expendable heavy-lift launch vehicle built by Khrunichev, using a common URM-1 core booster with four URM-1 strap-on boosters and a URM-2 second stage, topped by an upper stage such as Briz-M, Blok DM-03, or Persei. It made its maiden flight from Plesetsk on 23 December 2014 and has flown 5 times, with 4 successes and one partial failure when an upper stage failed to restart in December 2021. Its first flight from Vostochny Cosmodrome came in April 2024, and its first operational mission, carrying Kosmos 2589 and Kosmos 2590, flew in June 2025.",
    "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angara_A5",
    "as_of": "2026-07-13"
  },
